<subSubSection id="0EE6656EFFE32E4A9496FEE2FB4BE9CE" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="464336E5FFE32E4A9496FEE2FB0FE9ED" blockId="2.[151,1436,327,605]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="7488EAF7FFE32E4A9496FEE2FE91E941" bold="true" box="[151,273,327,352]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male imago: (
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A95B9FEEDFE44E941" box="[440,452,328,352]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
) forewing with costal and subcostal area orangish, longitudinal veins dark brown, cross veins strongly washed with black (
<figureCitation id="DEC72A60FFE32E4A961CFEC9FDE7E9A5" box="[541,615,364,389]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,2002,2024]" captionTargetBox="[176,1434,674,1961]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1448,657,1970]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hermanella amere, sp. nov., male imago. A) lateral view; B) dorsolateral view; C) prosternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284981/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs. 
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A965CFEC9FDE7E9A5" box="[605,615,364,388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A968FFEC9FD1DE9A5" box="[654,669,364,388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
A); (
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A96D0FEC9FD60E9A5" box="[721,736,364,388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
) subgenital plate yellow, with wide projection near inner base of forceps (
<figureCitation id="DEC72A60FFE32E4A951FFE2AFEE4E989" box="[286,356,399,424]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1961,1983]" captionTargetBox="[218,1387,224,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[183,1411,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hermanella amere, sp. nov., male imago. A) forewing; B) hind wing; C) enlarged hind wing; D) male genitalia, ventral view; E) detail of penes, ventral view; F) penis lobe, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284982/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A9554FE35FEE4E989" box="[341,356,400,424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D); (
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A959DFE35FE2AE989" box="[412,426,400,424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
) penes divided on distal half (
<figureCitation id="DEC72A60FFE32E4A9713FE2AFCD9E989" box="[786,857,399,424]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1961,1983]" captionTargetBox="[218,1387,224,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[183,1411,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hermanella amere, sp. nov., male imago. A) forewing; B) hind wing; C) enlarged hind wing; D) male genitalia, ventral view; E) detail of penes, ventral view; F) penis lobe, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284982/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Fig. 
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A974BFE35FCD9E989" box="[842,857,400,424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E); (
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A978CFE35FC1CE989" box="[909,924,400,424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="4.0">4</number>
) penis lobe with ventral, robust, posteriorly directed spine (
<figureCitation id="DEC72A60FFE32E4A9543FE11FE11E9ED" box="[322,401,436,461]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1961,1983]" captionTargetBox="[218,1387,224,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[183,1411,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hermanella amere, sp. nov., male imago. A) forewing; B) hind wing; C) enlarged hind wing; D) male genitalia, ventral view; E) detail of penes, ventral view; F) penis lobe, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284982/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs. 
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A9583FE11FE11E9ED" box="[386,401,436,460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E, F); (
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A95DEFE11FE6DE9EC" box="[479,493,436,461]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="5.0">5</number>
) general coloration of body yellowish orange (
<figureCitation id="DEC72A60FFE32E4A97FDFE11FBC6E9ED" box="[1020,1094,436,461]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,2002,2024]" captionTargetBox="[176,1434,674,1961]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1448,657,1970]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hermanella amere, sp. nov., male imago. A) lateral view; B) dorsolateral view; C) prosternum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284981/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Figs. 
<number id="F03424C2FFE32E4A903DFE11FBC6E9ED" box="[1084,1094,436,460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="464336E5FFE32E4A94C6FE72FB4BE9CE" blockId="2.[151,1436,327,605]" box="[199,1227,471,496]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="7488EAF7FFE32E4A94C6FE72FEDBE9D1" bold="true" box="[199,347,471,496]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Male imago.</emphasis>
Length: body, 
<quantity id="81049B00FFE32E4A9605FE72FD0EE9CE" box="[516,654,471,496]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.399999999999999" metricValueMax="8.6" metricValueMin="8.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="8.399999999999999" valueMax="8.6" valueMin="8.2">8.2–8.6 mm</quantity>
; forewing: 
<quantity id="81049B00FFE32E4A970CFE7DFC32E9CE" box="[781,946,472,496]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.075" metricValueMax="1.1199999999999999" metricValueMin="1.03" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="10.75" valueMax="11.2" valueMin="10.3">10.3–11.2 mm</quantity>
; hind wing: 
<quantity id="81049B00FFE32E4A903CFE72FB47E9CE" box="[1085,1223,471,496]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0EE6656EFFE32E4C94C6FE59FE24EBE9" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="464336E5FFE32E4A94C6FE59FCC1EA7C" blockId="2.[151,1436,327,605]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="7488EAF7FFE32E4A94C6FE59FE8DEA34" bold="true" box="[199,269,508,533]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Head.</emphasis>
Dorsal region yellowish, with brown marks; ventral region whitish, slightly washed with orange. Upper portion of compound eye orangish, lower portion black; ocelli whitish, surrounded by dark gray. 
<emphasis id="7488EAF7FFE32E4A90EDFD85FAC9EA16" box="[1260,1353,544,567]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Antenna</emphasis>
. Scape yellowish, pedicel brown, flagellum light yellow translucent.
</paragraph>
<caption id="1283666DFFE32E4A9496F877FB61EFC9" box="[151,1249,2001,2024]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/284981/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" targetBox="[176,1434,674,1961]" targetPageId="2">
